Avusa, Mondi Group, Mpact, Platmin May Move: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-07-11T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/avusa-mondi-group-mpact-platmin-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index lost 293.74, or 0.9
percent, to 32,002.33 in Johannesburg on July 8.  Avusa Ltd. (AVU)  : The newspaper publisher concluded a
due diligence agreement that will allow Capitau Holdings Plc to
assess if it wants to proceed with a takeover offer. Avusa was
unchanged at 24.60 rand.  Mvelaphanda Group Ltd. (MVG)  : The commercial services
provider sold 5.4 million shares in hospital company  Life
Healthcare Group Holdings Ltd. (LHC)  for 91.3 million rand. Mvela was
unchanged at 3.28 rand.  Mpact Ltd. (MPT SJ): The South African packaging company
owned by Mondi Group lists on the main board of the Johannesburg
stock exchange as it separates from its parent.  Mondi Plc (MNP)  rose 9
cents, or 0.1 percent, to 70.29 rand, while  Mondi Ltd. (MND)  climbed
60 cents, or 0.9 percent, to 69.50 rand.  Platmin Ltd. (PLN)  : The platinum miner said operations
resumed at its Pilanesberg Platinum Mine following a strike that
shut operations on June 24. Platmin fell 15 cents, or 3.7
percent, to 3.95 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
